Step 1: Exponential decay of concentration  
\[
c(x)=c_{0}e^{-k x}, 
\quad c(10\text{ cm})=\frac{c_{0}}{2}
\;\Longrightarrow\;
e^{-k\,(0.10)}=\tfrac12
\;\Longrightarrow\;
k=\frac{\ln2}{0.10\ \mathrm m}.
\]

Step 2: Thermodynamic force per mole  
\[
\mu(x)=\mu_{0}+RT\ln c(x)
\;\Longrightarrow\;
F=-\frac{d\mu}{dx}
=-RT\frac{d\ln c}{dx}
=RT\,k.
\]

Step 3: Numerical value at \(T=25^\circ\mathrm C=298\) K  
\[
F
=RT\,\frac{\ln2}{0.10}
=8.314\;\frac{\mathrm J}{\mathrm{mol\,K}}\times298\;\mathrm K
\times\frac{0.6931}{0.10\;\mathrm m}
\approx1.718\times10^{4}\;\frac{\mathrm N}{\mathrm{mol}}
