2. Moles of Li available from the cathode  
   \[
     n_{\mathrm{Li}} = n_{\mathrm{LiCoO_2}}
     = \frac{10.00\;\mathrm{g}}{97.87\;\mathrm{g/mol}}
     = 0.1022\;\mathrm{mol}
   \]

3. Formation of \(\mathrm{LiC_6}\) at the anode consumes 1 Li per formula unit and 6 C atoms:  
   \[
     n_{\mathrm{LiC_6}}
     = n_{\mathrm{Li}}
     = 0.1022\;\mathrm{mol}
   \]

4. Mass of \(\mathrm{LiC_6}\) formed  
   \[
     m_{\mathrm{LiC_6}}
     = n_{\mathrm{LiC_6}}\times M(\mathrm{LiC_6})
     = 0.1022\;\mathrm{mol}\times79.00\;\mathrm{g/mol}
     = 8.075\;\mathrm{g}
   \]

5. Graphite consumed:  
   \[
     n_{\mathrm{C,consumed}}
     = 6\times n_{\mathrm{LiC_6}}
     = 6\times0.1022\;\mathrm{mol}
     = 0.6132\;\mathrm{mol},
   \]
   Initial moles of C:  
   \[
     n_{\mathrm{C,init}}
