\]

Step 3:  Convert \(K\) to joules  
\[
K=0.4\ \mathrm{eV}\times1.602\times10^{-19}\,\mathrm{J/eV}
=6.408\times10^{-20}\,\mathrm{J}.
\]

Step 4:  Use \(K=\tfrac12 m_ev^2\) to solve for \(v\)  
\[
